## Decision Autonomy (Three Loops Model)

### Out-of-Loop (AI executes autonomously)
- Code formatting, linting fixes
- Import organization, unused variable removal
- Simple bug fixes with clear root cause
- Test additions for existing functions
- Documentation typo fixes

### On-the-Loop (AI proposes, human approves)
- New feature implementation (use Plan Mode)
- API endpoint changes (schema, routes, params)
- Database schema changes
- Dependency additions/upgrades
- Configuration changes
- Refactoring > 3 files

### In-the-Loop (Human decides, AI assists)
- Architecture decisions (new services, tech stack changes)
- Security model changes (auth, permissions, API keys)
- Deployment/infrastructure changes
- Data migration or deletion
- Public API breaking changes
- Cost-impacting decisions

## Development Protocol

### Feature Workflow (Spec-Driven)
1. `/spec-driven-dev` — Create spec for non-trivial features
2. Review spec with stakeholder (human In-the-Loop)
3. Plan Mode — generate implementation plan from spec
4. Implement in iterations (On-the-Loop)
5. `/governance-check` — Run fitness function checks
6. Merge with conventional commit

